Package: pvepci
Architecture: all
Depends: ${python3:Depends},
         ${misc:Depends},
         python3-yaml
Recommends: pve-manager
Description: manage PCI device assignments across Proxmox VE VMs
 pvepci moves PCI devices (in practice: GPUs) between Proxmox VE VMs in one
 command, instead of hand-editing every VM's config and power-cycling them by
 hand. It solves for the requested layout with the fewest VM restarts, and
 restarts exactly those VMs that were running beforehand.
 .
 Only PVE mapped resources are managed, so device identity is always a mapping
 name rather than a raw PCI address. Layouts come from named profiles in
 /etc/pve/pvepci.yaml or from ad-hoc command-line flags, and --dry-run shows
 exactly which configs change and which VMs stop and start.
 .
 Before stopping anything, pvepci checks whether a VM is actually in use:
 device utilization sampled over a window, logged-in users, long-running
 watchlisted processes, and uptime. It announces the shutdown inside the guest
 and gives users a veto file to cancel it.
 .
 This package must be installed on the Proxmox VE node itself, as it drives
 qm and pvesh locally.
